        public static final Tag create(Long id,
                               String title,
                               Long generationTime)
        Factory method to create an instance from the Interface Tag.

        The usage from the fluent builder TagBuilder is preferred against the directly usage from this method.

        • The first two attributes id and title are mandory.
        • Setting an value will be validate the value against DefaultTagValidator.
        This method delegates to create(java.lang.Long, java.lang.String, java.lang.Long, java.util.Optional, java.util.Optional) where all optional values are Optional.empty().
        Parameters:
        id - The id (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        title - The title (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        generationTime - The generationTime (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        Returns:
        A new instance from the Interface Tag.
        Since:
        0.1.0
        See Also:
        Tag, TagBuilder, DefaultTagValidator, Optional.empty()

      • create

        public static final Tag create(Long id,
                               String title,
                               Long generationTime,
                               Optional<String> description,
                               Optional<String> style)
        Factory method to create an instance from the Interface Tag.

        The usage from the fluent builder TagBuilder is preferred against the directly usage from this method.

        • The first two attributes id and title are mandory.
        • All other attributes are optional, that means if not set then Optional.empty() will returned.
        • Setting an value in a mandory or an optional attribute will be validate the value against DefaultTagValidator.
        Parameters:
        id - The id (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        title - The title (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        generationTime - The generationTime (mandory attribute) from this DefaultTag.
        description - Optional attribute. If not set then Optional#empty() will returned.
        style - Optional attribute. If not set then Optional#empty() will returned.
        Returns:
        A new instance from the Interface Tag.
        Since:
        0.1.0
        See Also:
        Tag, TagBuilder, DefaultTagValidator, Optional.empty()
